lementById('root')` \u2014 mounts React into `index.html` \n--- \n### 5.3 App.jsx \u2014 Navigation Controller \n```jsx \nimport React, { useState } from 'react'": null, " \nimport AgriPrimeDashboard from './screens/AgriPrimeDashboard'": null, " // ... 8 more imports \nconst NAV_ITEMS ": "[ \n\t { id: 'dashboard', label: 'Dashboard', icon: 'dashboard', component: AgriPrimeDashboard }, \n\t { id: 'livestock', label: 'Livestock', icon: 'pets',      component: LivestockManagement }, \n\t // ... 7 more items \n]", " \nexport default function App() { \n // \u2500\u2500 useState Hook \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500 \n const [activePage, setActivePage] ": "useState('dashboard')", "  const [collapsed, setCollapsed]   ": "useState(false)", " \n\n // Dynamic component rendering based on active state  const ActiveComponent ": null, " \n\t return ( \n\t\t <div style": null, " \n} \n``` \n--- \n### 5.4 React Hooks Used \n#### `useState` \u2014 State Management \n```jsx \n// In App.jsx \nconst [activePage, setActivePage] ": "useState('dashboard')", " // activePage ": null, " // Toggles between 'weekly' and 'monthly' for chart view ``` \n#### `useEffect` \u2014 Side Effects (Backend Integration) ```jsx \n// This would be used when connecting to the real API import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'": null, " \nfunction LivestockManagement() { \n const [animals, setAnimals] ": "useState([])", "  const [loading, setLoading] ": "useState(true)", " \n useEffect(() ": null, " \n\t\t\t setLoading(false)": null, " \n\t })": null, " \n }, [])": null, "   // [] ": "run once on mount only \n\t if (loading) return <div>Loading animals...</div>", " \n\t return animals.map(a ": null, " } \n``` \n--- \n### 5.5 Component Architecture \n``` \nApp.jsx (Root Component) \n\u2502 \n\u251c\u2500\u2500 <aside> \u2014 Sidebar Nav \n\u2502    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Maps over NAV_ITEMS array \u2192 renders nav buttons \n\u2502         onClick \u2192 setActivePage(item.id) \u2192 state changes \u2192 re-render \u2502 \n\u251c\u2500\u2500 <header> \u2014 Top Navigation Bar \n\u2502    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Haroon Sheikh \u00b7 Zamin In-Charge \u00b7 Search \u00b7 Notifications \u2502 \n\u2514\u2500\u2500 <main> \u2014 Content Area \n\t \u2514\u2500\u2500 <ActiveComponent /> (dynamically resolved) \n\t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 AgriPrimeDashboard      \u2192 Hero image + stats + chart \t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 LivestockManagement     \u2192 Animal table + search + filters \t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 VeterinaryBreedingCalendar \u2192 Calendar + health logs \t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 InventoryFeedControl    \u2192 Stock cards + reorder \n\t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 HRWorkerProfileDashboard \u2192 Employee cards + Kanban board \t\t \u251c\u2500\u2500 LogisticsDeliveryTracking \u2192 Map + route list \n```\n \u251c\u2500\u2500 FinancialProfitTracking \u2192 PKR revenue + transaction table  \u251c\u2500\u2500 AgriPrimeShopHome       \u2192 Product cards + hero banner  \u2514\u2500\u2500 EcommerceAdminDashboard \u2192 Order management table\n--- \n### 5.6 Key Dashboard Component Features \n```jsx \n// AgriPrimeDashboard.jsx \u2014 Key patterns: \n// 1. ARRAY MAP \u2014 renders 4 stat cards from data array \nconst stats ": "[ \n\t { label: 'Total Livestock', value: '1,284', icon: 'pets' }, \t { label: 'Health Alerts',   value: '03',    icon: 'emergency' }, \t // ... \n]", " \n\n{stats.map((s, i) ": null, " \n<button onClick": null, " React diffs it for efficient updates | When `setActivePage` changes, only the main content re-renders | \n| **SPA** | Single Page Application \u2014 no full page reloads | Navigation via state, not page loads | \n| **Key Prop** | Unique identifier for list items | `key": null, "  //  Blocks \n// With async: continues execution while waiting \nfs.readFile('file.txt', (err, data) ": "> {  //  Non-blocking \t console.log(data)", " \n// Modern async/await (used in controllers): \nconst animals ": "await Animal.find({})", "    // Non-blocking MongoDB query ``` \n#### NPM (Node Package Manager) \n```json \n// package.json \u2014 all dependencies for AgriPrime backend \n{ \n\t \"dependencies\": { \n\t\t \"express\":          \"^4.18.2\",  // Web framework \n\t\t \"mongoose\":         \"^7.5.0\",   // MongoDB ODM \n\t\t \"cors\":             \"^2.8.5\",   // Cross-origin headers \n\t\t \"dotenv\":           \"^16.3.1\",  // Environment variables \n\t\t \"jsonwebtoken\":     \"^9.0.2\",   // JWT authentication \n\t\t \"bcryptjs\":         \"^2.4.3\",   // Password hashing \n\t\t \"morgan\":           \"^1.10.0\"   // HTTP request logger \n\t }, \n\t \"devDependencies\": { \n\t\t \"nodemon\": \"^3.0.1\"             // Auto-restart server on changes \t }, \n\t \"scripts\": { \n\t\t \"start\":  \"node server.js\", \n\t\t \"dev\":    \"nodemon server.js\"   // npm run dev \u2192 starts backend \t } \n} \n``` \n\n#### Environment Variables (`.env`) \n```env \nMONGO_URI": null, " \n// Register: hash password before saving \nconst hashedPassword ": "await bcrypt.hash(req.body.password, 10)", "  // 10 ": null, " ``` \n--- \n## 9. Anticipated Viva Questions & Answers \n### Q1: What is the MERN stack? \n> **A:** MERN is a full-stack JavaScript framework consisting of: > - **M**ongoDB \u2014 NoSQL document database \n> - **E**xpress.js \u2014 backend web framework for Node.js \n> - **R**eact.js \u2014 frontend UI library \n> - **N**ode.js \u2014 JavaScript server runtime \n> All components use JavaScript, allowing full-stack development in one language. \n--- \n### Q2: Why did you choose MongoDB over MySQL for this project? \n> **A:** AgriPrime manages diverse data types \u2014 animal records, medical histories, financial transactions, employee payroll, and marketplace orders. MongoDB's **flexible schema** allows us to store these varied documents without forcing rigid table relationships. Also, MongoDB stores data as JSON-like BSON documents, which maps naturally to JavaScript objects used on both the React frontend and Node.js backend. \n--- \n### Q3: Explain the difference between SQL and NoSQL. \n| | SQL (MySQL) | NoSQL (MongoDB) | \n|--|------------|-----------------| \n| Structure | Fixed schema (tables/rows) | Flexible schema (documents) | | Query Language | SQL | MongoDB Query Language / Mongoose | \n| Relationships | Foreign keys, JOIN | Embedded docs or ObjectId \nreferences | \n| Scale | Vertical | Horizontal | \n| Best For | Structured, relational data | Unstructured, hierarchical data | \n--- \n### Q4: What is `useState` and how is it used in AgriPrime? \n> **A:** `useState` is a React Hook that lets a component manage its own internal state. In `App.jsx`: \n> ```jsx \n> const [activePage, setActivePage] ": "useState('dashboard')", " \n> ``` \n> When a user clicks \"Livestock\" in the sidebar, \n`setActivePage('livestock')` is called. React re-renders the component, and `ActiveComponent` dynamically resolves to `LivestockManagement`, showing that screen without any page reload. \n--- \n\n### Q5: What is the difference between `useEffect` and `useState`? \n> - **`useState`** \u2014 stores and manages data that changes within a component. When updated, triggers a re-render. \n> - **`useEffect`** \u2014 runs **side effects** (API calls, DOM manipulation, subscriptions) after the component renders. Used with a dependency array `[]` to control when it runs. \n--- \n### Q6: How does navigation work in AgriPrime without React Router? \n> **A:** AgriPrime uses **state-driven navigation** via `useState`. The `NAV_ITEMS` array maps each module ID to its React component. When a nav item is clicked, `setActivePage(item.id)` updates state, and: \n> ```jsx \n> const ActiveComponent ": null, " \n> ``` \n> This resolves the correct component dynamically. The sidebar re-renders with the active highlight, and the main area swaps content. **React Router** would be used for URL-based routing (useful when we need \nshareable links like `/dashboard`, `/livestock`). \n--- \n### Q7: What is the MVC pattern and how does AgriPrime follow it? \n> **A:** MVC ": "Model, View, Controller \n> - **Model** \u2014 Mongoose schemas (`Animal`, `Employee`, `Order`) define data structure \n> - **View** \u2014 React components (`AgriPrimeDashboard.jsx`, \n`LivestockManagement.jsx`) render the UI \n> - **Controller** \u2014 Express controller functions (`animalController.js`) handle business logic between the Model and View \n--- \n### Q8: What is Mongoose and why use it instead of the native MongoDB driver? \n> **A:** Mongoose is an ODM (Object Document Mapper) that provides: > 1. **Schema definition** \u2014 enforce structure and validation \n> 2. **Models** \u2014 OOP interface (`Animal.find()`, `Animal.create()`) > 3. **Middleware (hooks)** \u2014 run code before/after save, delete \n> 4. **Virtuals & Computed fields** \n> The native `MongoClient` is lower-level and requires manual validation. Mongoose abstracts this complexity. \n--- \n### Q9: How would you handle user authentication in AgriPrime? \n> **A:** \n> 1. **Register:** User submits email + password \u2192 bcrypt hashes password \u2192 stored in `users` collection \n> 2. **Login:** Password compared with bcrypt \u2192 if match, JWT signed with `jwt.sign({userId}, secret, {expiresIn: '7d'})` \n\n> 3. **Protected routes:** React sends `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header \n> 4. **Backend middleware:** `jwt.verify(token, secret)` decodes it \u2192 attaches `req.user` \u2192 allows access \n> 5. **Logout:** React clears the token from localStorage \n--- \n### Q10: What is the difference between `PUT` and `PATCH`? \n> - **`PUT`** \u2014 Replaces the **entire resource**. You must send all fields. Missing fields become null. \n> - **`PATCH`** \u2014 Partial update. Only send the fields you want to change. \n> In AgriPrime, updating an animal's weight uses `PATCH /api/animals/:id` with just `{weightKg: 590}`. \n--- \n### Q11: What is CORS and why is it needed? \n> **A:** CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a browser security mechanism that blocks HTTP requests from one origin (domain:port) to another. Since React runs on port **5173** and Express runs on port **5000**, the browser blocks communication by default. Adding `cors()` middleware to Express sends the header `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: http://localhost:5173` which tells the browser to allow the request. \n--- \n### Q12: What is the Virtual DOM? \n> **A:** React creates an in-memory JavaScript representation of the actual browser DOM. When state changes (e.g., clicking Financial in the sidebar), React creates a new Virtual DOM tree, **diffs** it against the old one using the **reconciliation algorithm**, and only applies the **minimal changes** to the real DOM. This avoids expensive full DOM re-renders and makes React applications fast. \n--- \n### Q13: Explain the data flow in a MERN app. \n> ``` \n> User clicks \"Livestock\" \u2192 \n> React setActivePage('livestock') \u2192 \n> LivestockManagement mounts \u2192 \n> useEffect calls fetch('/api/animals') \u2192 \n> Express router handles GET /api/animals \u2192 > Controller queries MongoDB via Mongoose \u2192 > Animal.find({}) returns array of documents \u2192 > Controller sends JSON response \u2192 \n> React receives data \u2192 setAnimals(data) \u2192 > Component re-renders with animal list \u2192 \n> User sees the table \n> ``` \n--- \n\n### Q14: Why use Vite instead of Create React App? \n> - **Vite** uses **ES Modules** natively in the browser during \ndevelopment \u2014 no bundling step needed \n> - Starts in milliseconds vs. seconds for CRA \n> - Hot Module Replacement (HMR) is near-instant \n> - `npm run dev` in the project starts Vite dev server on port **5173** \n--- \n### Q15: What are the 9 modules of AgriPrime and their purpose? \n> 1. **Dashboard** \u2014 KPI overview with Pakistani farm hero image \n> 2. **Livestock** \u2014 RFID-based animal tracking (breed, weight, health status) \n> 3. **Veterinary** \u2014 Vaccination schedule, breeding calendar, treatment logs \n> 4. **Inventory** \u2014 Feed stock levels, reorder alerts, supplier \nmanagement \n> 5. **HR & Payroll** \u2014 Employee profiles, task board (Kanban), \nattendance & salary (PKR) \n> 6. **Logistics** \u2014 Delivery route management, driver assignment, tracking \n> 7. **Financial** \u2014 Revenue \u20a8240M, expenses \u20a8160M, profit \u20a880M tracking with transactions \n> 8. **Marketplace** \u2014 E-commerce storefront for organic farm produce > 9. **Order Management** \u2014 Order fulfillment, status tracking, customer management \n--- \n## 10. Tech Stack Summary Table \n| Layer | Technology | Version | Role | \n|-------|-----------|---------|------| \n| **Database** | MongoDB Atlas | 7.x | NoSQL cloud database | \n| **ODM** | Mongoose | 7.x | Schema + MongoDB interface | \n| **Server** | Node.js | 20.x | JavaScript runtime | \n| **Framework** | Express.js | 4.x | REST API framework | \n| **Auth** | JWT + bcrypt | latest | Authentication & security | | **Frontend** | React.js | 18.x | UI component library | \n| **Build Tool** | Vite | 5.x | Fast bundler & dev server | \n| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS | 3.x | Utility-first CSS framework | | **Icons** | Material Symbols | latest | Google's icon font | | **Fonts** | Inter + Manrope | latest | Premium typography | \n| **State** | React useState | \u2014 | Navigation & UI state | \n| **Localization** | PKR (\u20a8) + Pakistani names | \u2014 | Local context | | **Environment** | dotenv | 16.x | Environment variables | \n| **Dev Tool** | nodemon | 3.x | Backend auto-restart | \n| **HTTP Client** | fetch() / axios | \u2014 | React \u2192 Express calls | \n--- \n##  Quick Revision Cheat Sheet \n\n``` \nMongoDB   \u2192 Document database \u2192 JSON-like BSON \u2192 Collections \u2192 Mongoose ODM \nExpress   \u2192 REST API \u2192 Routes \u2192 Controllers \u2192 Middleware (CORS, JWT, JSON) \nReact     \u2192 Components \u2192 JSX \u2192 useState \u2192 useEffect \u2192 Virtual DOM \u2192 SPA Node.js   \u2192 Server runtime \u2192 Non-blocking I/O \u2192 npm \u2192 async/await \u2192 dotenv \nAgriPrime Flow: \n User Action \u2192 React state \u2192 API fetch \u2192 Express route \u2192  Controller \u2192 Mongoose query \u2192 MongoDB \u2192 JSON response \u2192  React setState \u2192 Component re-render \u2192 Updated UI \n9 Modules: Dashboard \u00b7 Livestock \u00b7 Veterinary \u00b7 Inventory \u00b7 HR \u00b7 Logistics \u00b7 Financial \u00b7 Marketplace \u00b7 Orders \nCurrency: \u20a8 PKR  |  Names: Haroon Sheikh, Fatima Malik, Usman Ahmed, Tariq Hassan, Sara Khan \nAuth: JWT Bearer Token \u2192 bcrypt password hash \u2192 protected routes ``` \n--- \n*Document prepared for AgriPrime MERN Stack Project Viva \u2014 April 2026* *Frontend: React + Vite (Fully Implemented) | Backend: Node + Express + MongoDB (Designed & Ready)*"}